Grand Hotel TeleMat Station

 - - - Someone arriving at the Grand Hotel TeleMat Station a hundred years ago would have been impressed with the marble tiles on the floor, the gilt edging along the walls, the graceful curves of the arches over the booths. A century later the peeling tiles showed the marble-effect was only paper thin, the gilt had long since been scratched off, though the curves remained.
> w

 - - - The Grand Hotel... Back in the thirtieth century this place might have been grand, but nowadays it looked worn and old.

Grand Hotel (Lobby)

 - - - Vic stood in the lobby of the Grand Hotel; a large open area with a high ceiling. The carpet, a blue Paisy-like design, was faded, and looking worn in the doorways. To the east, there was an archway leading to the TeleMat station, to the north, a large window looked out on the starport. Automatic doors to the south led to Star Avenue. To the west, there was a row of lifts giving access to the floor above, and a long reception desk. A woman in blue uniform sat behind the desk filing her nails; her name badge indicated she was called Mandy.
> ask mandy about maisy

 - - - "I'm looking for Maisy DeValle," said Vic.

 - - - "Yeah, you and all the New Chicago police force. What makes you think I know anything about her?"
> ask mandy about leona

 - - - "I'm looking for Leona Jones," said Vic.

 - - - "Yeah? Leona Jones... Yeah, we got a Leona Jones. Who shall I say it is?"

 - - - "Gantry. Vic Gantry."

 - - - Mandy picked up her phone, and spoke to it. "Miss Jones? There's a Vic Gantry wants to see you... Okay." She out the phone down. "Seems she wants to see you. Room 423; take the elevator." With that she returned to filing her nails.
> u

 - - - Vic got the lift up to the fourth floor. Room 423 was a short way down the corridor, on the right. He knocked, and entered.

Grand Hotel (Room 423)

 - - - Maisy's room was like any other at the hotel. The AutoCleans kept it spotless, but could not hide the faded glory. There was a double bed, a dresser, two chairs, and a very small bathroom. On the dresser, Vic could see the remains of a meal. Maisy was sat on the bed.
> ask maisy about myothian falcon

 - - - "What do you know about something called the Myothian Falcon? I think it was taken when your husband was murdered."

 - - - "That?" She shrugged. "It looked like a glass bird, nothing special. My husband got it about six months ago."
