> ask linda about files

 - - - "If I had a little problem with some encrypted files, you'd be able to help me I guess. Its about that data key I gave you, you see, and an innocent women could go to the chair if I fail..."

 - - - Linda smiled. "No promises, but I'd be happy to try, Vic. It'll be nice working together." She took the key from Vic, and put it into her computer. "I'm going to go via a couple of other servers to hide my tracks, so it might take a few moments." A few minutes later: "We're in; what do you want to see?"

 - - - "Anything unusual, anything odd for a rich, happily married guy."

 - - - "That's a bit vague... Okay, six months ago he paid a large sum of money to a guy called George Lancing, 450,000 credits. Few payments to something called Green Heaven... Here's something, he pays rent on an apartment in Twenty Third Street - Camden Towers, room 312. Why would a guy who lives in a big mansion want an apartment in that district?"

 - - - "That's a very interesting question."
