Jonty Hall (Ground Floor)

 - - - Jonty Hall was an accommodation block for staff and students wanting to live on campus. It was much like any regular apartment block, and kept in a good state of cleanliness. Vic noticed the door to the west had a plaque, with 'Dr Lancing' inscribed on it.
> w

Dr. Lancing's Apartment

 - - - Even before he entered the apartment, Vic could tell something was wrong. He could smell death even at the doorway. Inside, the large apartment was a mess, but what drew Vic's eyes was the corpse. Somebody, presumably Dr Lancing lay, in the middle of the room, spread-eagled, and very dead, with a spear in his chest.
> look at body

 - - - Dr. Lancing's body looked to have been carefully laid out, with his arms and legs spread-eagled. He would have been about forty, Vic judged, with dark and and moustache, and was wearing red pyjamas. A spear was buried deep in his chest, his eyes wide open with fear. From the smell, Vic guessed he had been dead a couple of days at least, which meant he had been murdered before Lawrence DeValle.
> look at spear

 - - - The spear protuding from Dr. Lancing's chest was made of thick wood. Vic could not see the head of it at all, but the shaft was inscribed with writing, though in a script unlike any he had seen before. Red ribbons had been tied around it at three points along the shaft, close to where it entered the body.
> take spear

 - - - Vic would have liked to take the spear to show to Prof Kant, but the cops would call it interfering with evidence; instead he took some photos on his iJot.
> e

