 - - - Vic knocked twice on the door, heard a "Come in", and walked into Prof Kant's office.

Prof Kant's office

 - - - Prof Kant's office was small and functional; somehow Vic had expected something more fancy for an academic. The entire west wall was covered with newspaper printouts. Prof Kant was sat at a desk; she looked up from her computer.
> tell kant about lancing

 - - - Vic confronted Prof. Kant directly. "I've some bad news about Dr Lancing, Professor. I called at his apartment, and found the door ajar. Inside, well, it wasn't pretty, I can tell you. Been dead a couple of days at least."

 - - - "How awful..." She looked pale as milk. "He was not exactly a friend, but still I knew him well; it's hard to believe... Well, hard to believe it happened here on the campus, and not in the Uralgan jungle. Have you informed the police?"

 - - - "Under the circumstances, I thought it would sound better coming from you."

 - - - "I suppose you're right. If you could see yourself out, I shall do that directly."
> ask kant about spear

 - - - Vic wanted to handle this delicately. "There was a spear in Dr. Lancing's apartment with writing on it." He showed her the photo on his iJot. "Can you tell me anything about it?"

 - - - "Let me see. Well, it's a Uralgan script, I can tell you that much. If it was written recently, I would place it around 200 miles from here. The Uralgans had a very simple alphabet before we arrived; slowly they are adopting English characters into their own written language to cover the deficiencies. See here, an "e", and this is an "r". The more English characters, the nearer the city it comes from. No idea what it means, sorry."
> ask kant about myothian falcon

 - - - "I'm interested in an artefact Dr Lancing found, the Myothian Falcon. Would you know anything about that?"

 - - - "I've never heard of it, but let me check the database. Any items found on an expedition are carefully catelogued." She consulted her computer, then shook her head. "No, nothing. The only thing I can tell you is that Myothi is a Uralgan nation. Hmm, you might want to talk to Ursula Nguyen; she was Dr Lancing's Post-Doc; I suppose I'll have to re-assign her. She's probably in the lab."
> ask kant about date

 - - - "You're a remarkable woman, Professor. I was wonder if perhaps you'd like to have dinner with me some time?"

 - - - "Goodness me, I'm old enough to be your mother." She shrugged. "Then again, why not? That would be lovely."
> s

Dept History and Archaeology (Lobby)

 - - - The foyer of the History and Archaeology Department was grand and imposing. A series of free standing pillars contained holograms of historical events. Posters on the wall proclaimed forth-coming events, many that had long since happened, Vic noted. Stairs led up to the lecture halls, while a sign to the north east indicated the laboratory lay that way. There were offices; to the north, Prof Kant's, and to the west, Dr. Lancing's. A secretary, Una, sat at a desk. The building exit was though large glass doors to the southwest.
> ne

Dept History and Archaeology (Post Graduate Lab)

 - - - Vic had an image in his head of a laboratory where people in white coats worked at benches doing experiments. This was not at all like that; just two rows of desks with computers on them, and students doing their research on the internet. Ursula was at the third desk on the right.
> ask ursula about lancing

 - - - "I hear Dr Lancing is your supervisor. Do you mind if I ask you to tell me about him?"

 - - - Ursula sniffed sadly. "Oh, he was a wonderful man. All the other lecturers were jealous of him, because he was the only one willing to do field work. I bet it was one of them.  Oh, God, I can't believe he's dead." She started to sob quietly.
> ask ursula about myothian falcon

 - - - "Do you know anything about an artefact Dr Lancing found a few months ago, something called the Myothian Falcon?"

 - - - "Oh, yes, that," sighed Ursula. "It was on an expedition seven months. We found it on the central altar inside the ancient Temple of Irithea. Dr Lancing called it the Myothian Falcon because it kind of looked like a falcon. The natives said it had some strange powers, and Dr Lancing pretended to go a bit loopy when he picked it up."

 - - - "Loopy?"

 - - - "Yeah, like he could see terrible monsters."

 - - - "You sure he was just kidding?"

 - - - "Yes! I was carrying it half the time; I can assure you I saw no monsters."

 - - - "Did anyone else know about the Falcon?"

 - - - She shrugged. "I don't know. .. Yes, there was a guy called Barry asking about it a couple of weeks ago. No, not Barry; Larry, that was it. Real seedy looking guy. Larry Yang. Oh, yes, and Lawence DeValle, that dead guy; I heard Dr Lancing talking to him about it shortly after we got back. Hey, is that what this is about?"
> ask ursula about date

 - - - "Say you fancy going to get a bite to eat later?"

 - - - "You mean like a date? You're old enough to be my dad!"
> sw

