Bureau Street TeleMat Station

 - - - The TeleMat station for the main administration area, this was one of the largest in the city, and at rush hour it would be a seething mass of people. Right now, it was relatively quiet.
> w

Bureau Street

 - - - Vic stood in Bureau Street and looked about. This was where much of the administration of New Chicago was, including the police station, right across from the TeleMat station, to the west. To the right of the police station, there was a bar, "Donegal's Authentic Irish Bar"; that was where Vic was most likely to find Detective Munroe. A temporary stall had been set up beside the TeleMat station by some enterprising guy by the name of Pierre, offering flowers for the busy office workers to take home to their loved ones.
> nw

Donegal's Authentic Irish Bar

 - - - As Vic surveyed Donegal's Irish Bar, he wondered just how authentic this place was. Would a real Irish pub have shamrock shaped tables, and videos of "Riverdance" on every available wall? The customers were a mix of business men and cops; even those who were not in suits or uniform looked to be plainclothes cops to Vic's experienced eye. As expected, Munroe was here, his old partner from his brief time as a cop.
> ask munroe about maisy

 - - - "So what do you know about Maisy DeValle," Vic asked casually.

 - - - Jill gave him a look. "Is this about a case, Vic? You do know we have an APB out on her. If you knew where she was, you would tell me, right?"

 - - - "I was just curious, what with it being in the papers. So what about her?"

 - - - "Well, all the evidence's against her. She stands to inherit a ton, and we know she was at the house when her husband died, and she did a runner after the murder. Still waiting for the forenics, but she's as good as fried."
> ask munroe about cigarette

 - - - "Your boys found anything on that cigarette end yet, Jill?"

 - - - "Give them a chance, Vic. You know we're all ploughed under with work."
> ask munroe about lancing

 - - - "So what did you find out about Lancing?"

 - - - "You know I can't tell you about that, Vic."

 - - - "I know the official line, but this connects to a case I'm working on. We both want the sme thing here, Jill, to see the right people go to court. So if you happened to let something slip in conversation with an old friend..."

 - - - "Well, as long as that old friend never let on where he heard it... Lancing was stabbed to death with with two different knives, the spear was added as decoration once he was dead. The room was then ransacked; at this point we haven't discovered anything that might be missing; it was not a burglary gone wrong as far as we can tell. DNA indicates two Uralgans, and security cameras confirm two Uralgans entering and leaving the building three days ago, at 0432 and 0456 respectively. TeleMat records indicate they arrived from Twenty Third Street and returned there."
