 - - - Vic looked up and down Twenty Third Avenue. It was busy, but then it was always business. Most street corners had a hooker or two touting for business, and the shops were all offering sex or gambling or some either vice, or were just boarded shut. He did not know why, but the steeet always seemed to have more than the usual number of Uralgans.
> s

Twenty Third Avenue (South)

 - - - The south end of Twenty Third Avenue was the most run down. The 'Lion's Den', at the north end, might be a dive, but it had a seedy glamour that attracted the better class of scum. At this end, the shops were tattier, the people more miserable and the whores cheaper. To the southeast, Vic noticed a derelict shop; 'Marty's Fashion Boutique'.

 - - - On one side of the street, a man was telling all who would listen that they were damned to hell unless they adopted his personal brand of religion. Vic wondered if any ever did listen to people like that.
> w

Camden Towers

 - - - Camden Towers was a run-down apartment block, put up early in the last century. When built, it had pretentions of attracting a smart crowd, and the apartments had been well-appointed. As the Twenty Third Avenue district had slid down the drain, the better residents had left, the rent had dropped, and the owners had stopped bothering to maintain the place. Now the stairwells were full of litter, the walls were stained with various dubious liquids, and everywhere smelt of urine. Room 312 would be up on the third floor.
> u

Camden Towers (Room 312)

 - - - Petharla's apartment was just one room in what would have been a suite of rooms; this would probably have been a bedroom. There was a window, a bed, two chairs, and a cupboard, and one door if he wanted to go back down.

 - - - The lift was out of order, and looked like it had been for many years. Vic walked up the three flights of stairs, carefuly picking his way between the junk, excrement and occasional vagrant. There was apartment 312; the name on the door was Petharla. He knocked and a Uralgan girl, presumably Petharla, let him in.
> ask petharla about lawrence

 - - - "Do you know a guy called Lawrence DeValle?"

 - - - "I... yes, I did. Oh, gods, what does it matter now? We were lovers." Her shuddering grew worse. "He was a wonderful man, so warm and caring. He was going to divorce his wife, and marry me - before that heartless bitch killed him. He didn't even like human women, did you know that?"

 - - - "He rented this apartment for you?"

 - - - "Just temporarily, while he worked things out."

 - - - "When did you last see him?"

 - - - "Only last night..." More shuddering. "Just a few hours ago I was lying in his arms..."

 - - - "Really? So when he was murdered he was on his way home from here then. Say, that might account for the security system..."

 - - - "Oh he always turned off the security when he was coming here, so his horrible wife would not see him leaving. Is that important?"
> ask petharla about myothian falcon

 - - - "Ever heard of something called the Myothian Falcon?"

 - - - "No." She shook her head. "What is it?"
> d

 - - - "I'll see myself out," said Vic, leaving the apartment. Carefully he picked his way down to the lobby.

