 - - - Now he was at north end of Twenty Third Avenue, Vic could see the 'Lion's Den', an almost legit casino on the east side of the road. As he watched, a man and a woman walked in. Lambs to the slaughter, thought Vic, shaking his head.

 - - - A gust of wind set a fast food wrapper tumbling down the street.
> ne

Dark Alley

 - - - The back street was basically a gap between buildings, allowing service access to them. To the west, Twenty Third Avenue, to the east, a dead end. This was the domain of the garbage canister and the fire escape.
> u

Garbage Canister

 - - - Vic was now stood on top of the garbage canister. He was probably high enough to reach the fire escape; unfortunately it was on the other side of the alley.
> leap

 - - - Vic leapt for the fire escape, but it was too far away, too high up, and he landed, a little awkwardly, on the ground.

Dark Alley

 - - - The back street was basically a gap between buildings, allowing service access to them. To the west, Twenty Third Avenue, to the east, a dead end. This was the domain of the garbage canister and the fire escape.
> push canister

 - - - With some effort, Vic pushed the garbage canister under the Lion's Den fire escape. You would think something on wheels would be a bit easier to shift, he thought to himself.
> u

Garbage Canister

 - - - Vic was now stood on top of the garbage canister, under the fire escape.
> jump

 - - - Vic jumped up, grabbing hold of the fire escape, and swinging himself up.

Lion's Den (Fire Escape)

 - - - Vic was stood on a platform someway up the north side of Lion's Den; a fire escape from the upper floor. There was no door to the building; presumably in the event of a fire people were supposed to climb out the window.
> examine window

 - - - Vic peered through the grimy window. It was hard to see through, but he could make out a desk and a chair; there seemed to be no people in it. He also checked the window itself. He could find no trace of an alarm on it, and the lock looked positively antiquated. Perhaps Stom relied on her reputation as a vicious and vindictive bitch to deter burglars.
> in

Lion's Den (Office)

 - - - The office was a strange mix of rich and poor. The cream paint on the walls and ceiling was flaking so badly, Vic could see that it used to be painted aqua, and before that olive green. However, the furnishings were all very high class. A Hetu-style desk, with matching chair, paintings on the walls looked to be originals - or at least expensive copies - the rugs on the floor were deep and soft. There was a single door to the east, and Vic thought he could hear footsteps out there; a window to the north led to the fire escape.

 - - - Vic gently eased the window open, still looking carefully for any evidence of an alarm system. Then he quietly climbed inside.
> open desk

 - - - Vic opened the heti-style desk.

 - - - The desk contained a Myothian Falcon.
> get falcon

 - - - The footsteps beyond the door were getting closer; he had to work fast. Quickly he picked up the Myothian Falcon, but at that moment the door burst open, and... something entered the room. It was the stuff of nightmares, a beast of some sort, but its form was constantly shifting; at first dog-like, now more avian, and then perhaps like a dragon. Whatever its true shape, it struck fear in Vic's heart like nothing ever had before.
> drop falcon

 - - - With some effort of will, Vic put down the Myothian Falcon. As he did so, the nightmeare beast became more solid, assuming just one form; a man. Specifically Doug Kalto, one of Stom's goons. He was looking at Vic. "I said, what are you doing in Ms Stom's office?"
> get falcon

 - - - "I'm just here to pick this up,", said Vic, as he lifted up the Myothian Falcon again. For a moment Kalto seemed to be thinking about changed into a giant spider, before changing his mind, and keeping his man shape.

 - - - "I don't think so," said Kalto
> give falcon to doug

 - - - "Perhaps you should have this." Vic handed the Myothian Falcon to Kalto.

 - - - "Maybe I sh... No, no. Getting away from me!" His eyes wide with terror, Kalto dropped the Myothian Falcon and fled the room.
> get falcon

 - - - Vic picked up the Myothian Falcon, and as he did, the room lurched around his, everything around him taking a new form, but only briefly, then turning back to normal.
> n

 - - - Vic opened the window again, and climbed out on to the fire ecape.

