Derelict Clothing Shop

 - - - The shop interior was a mess. It looked like the last tenant had left pretty quickly; there were racks still with clothes on them, though most were in a pretty poor shape. There was also evidence of more recent occupation; blankets laid out on the floor, on top of more of the old merchandise; the remains of a meal.

 - - - Two Uralgans, a man and a woman, emerged from the darkness at the back on the room; this must be Kalal and Erida-Pa, though Vic. "Who are you, what do you want?", asked Kalal; he did not sound exactly friendly.
> ask erida-pa about falcon

 - - - "Can I ask you a question," Vic said to Erida-Pa. She narrowed her eyes at her.

 - - - "She will not speak to you," said Kalal. "She is a holy person, for her to speak in your language would be a blasphemy. It is shameful for me too, but I do it because I must."
> ask kalal about falcon

 - - - "You know about something called the Myothian Falcon."

 - - - "Hah! What you call the Myothian Falcon is the embodiment of the goddess Irithea. The theft of this most holy thing is deeply insulting to all Uralgans, and especially the Myothi! Even for a man to hold it is considered a blasphemy."
