The Lion's Den (Lobby)

 - - - Vic looked around the dimly lit lobby of the Lion's Den. While the interior might have been dressed up, no one had bothered with this area; the blue paint was flaking from the walls, the concrete floors were scratched and marked. An archway to the north led to the casino. A large guy in a suit eyed him suspiciously. "You ain't a cop, are you? We don't take kindly to cops in here."
