Opulent Boulevard TeleMat Station

 - - - Vic was stood on the concourse at Opulent Boulevard transit. It was noticeably cleaner than most, and quiet too. Not only were fewer people using the booths, but there was little noise coming from the street. The usual hum of city was muted here.
> n

Opulent Boulevard

 - - - Originally named after Jackie O'Poole, one of the original settlers, the name Opulent Boulevard became popular as more and more of the city's ultra-rich moved here. Opulent Boulevard ran some way out of the city into the Uralgan jungle - far enough to allow the residents to feel removed from the common man, but still close enough to the safety of the city. The road was quiet; Vic could see no one for several blocks. Both sides were lined with jacaranda trees, and behind them the high walls surrounded the various mansions. The DeValle mansion was off to the east.
> e

Opulent Boulevard (East)

 - - - Vic stood outside the gates to the DeValle mansion. The cop at the entrance had gone now, and looking up the drive, Vic could see the one at the door was not there either.
> n

DeValle Mansion (Front Garden)

 - - - Vic stood on the red brick path leading up to the house. From here, he could see the front door of the house well, while the gate was behind him.
> n

DeValle Mansion (Great Hall)

 - - - This was a large room, panelled in dark wood, dominated by a grand staircase, rising to the upper story. The staircase was carpeted in red, but the floor was tiled in an ornate geometric pattern. That will have made cleaning the blood off easier, thought Vic ruefully; it was all but gone now. Maisy DeValle was here, waiting to talk to Vic.
> ask maisy about money

 - - - "I'm glad to see you back in your own home, Mrs DeValle. Did the cops tell you it was a guy called Bram Fenton? He was stealing the Myothian Falcon," Vic indicated the empty niche that it had been taken from, "and Mr DeValle was in the wrong place at the wrong time."

 - - - "Thank you very much, Mr Gantry. Yes, it's wonderful to be back, but the house is so empty without Lawrence... But anyway, you'll be wanting your money I expect. The remaining 500 credits, and an extra 500 for being so quick."

 - - - "That's great, Mrs DeValle."
> journal

 - - - Vic felt sure he was on the right trail, but what now? He got out his iJot, and reviewed what he had learnt so far.
I have a new case at last! Maisy DeValle, on the run, found husband dead at bottom of stairs in pool of blood; check house on Opulent B
Maisy staying in Grand Hotel as Leona Jones
Met Linda Love in other office; does message encryption
 Got a date with Linda Love at L'Escargots; just hope I can afford the prices
Found matchbook from Lion's Den, someone watching the house?
Found cigarette near DeValle mansion; remember to give to Jill
Study window forced, murderer's access?
Body gone, but a lot of blood; what a mess
Something stolen from hall? Myothian Falcon ?!? See Dr Lancing at uni arch dept
Weapon: YP-33; not common; ask Mickey
Telemat logs; two men arrive at Opulent, a man and a Uralgan leave, all separately?!?
DeValle paid 450k cr to George Lancing; pays regular money to Green Heaven; has apartment 312 in Camden Towers
Talked to Prof Kant, brother of Clive from Pentown bombing case
Dr Lancing dead, spear in chest
Spear has Uralgan writing
Ursula Nguyen, postdoc for lancing
M Falcon causes delusion?!?
Mickey says only Bram Fenton still uses YP-33
Two Myothi Uralgan's in Marty's clothes shop; Kalal and Erida-Pa
Petharla says DeValle regular turned off the security himself so Maisy would not discover he was going off at night to see his bit of fluff
Found M Falcon in Lion's Den office; hallucinations; did Fenton see them too?
Cigarette smoked by Bram Fenton; petty criminal; Nikki Stom's
Talked to Maisy; got paid; case over
> give falcon to maisy

 - - - "I'm not sure who this really belongs to," said Vic, handing the Myothian Falcon to Maisy, "but it was stolen from your house, so I'm giving it to you."

 - - - "Thank you, Mr Gantry. It is absolutely beautiful. It's strange, I never noticed that before. But I think the right place for this is in its temple, in Myothi."

 - - - "Perhaps you could take it there. They seem a bit touchy about a guy holding it, so you might like to play down my involvement."

 - - - "I'd be delighted to, Mr Gantry."

 - - - The case was solved, Vic had been paid and the Myothian Falcon returned. A good day's work, he considered.

 - - - . . . THE END ! . . .
